          "date": "2026-03-31 05:46:27.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-930 doc: update lctl-set_param with more details",
        "message": "LU-930 doc: update lctl-set_param with more details\n\nBe more specific about the semantics of which parameters the\n\"lctl set_param\" command will be affecting when it is run with\ndifferent arguments.  It wasn't very clear from the previous\ntext that using '-P' on the MGS was the primary way of setting\nthe parameters for the whole filesystem.\n\nAdd a section about bash-completion so that users can learn\nabout this very useful functionality for set_param, get_param,\nlist_param, and lfs find.\n\nFix some minor checkpatch-man warnings.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\nChange-Id: If811eb53caa9d842edf2dba746f6c57039500c1e\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/64405\nReviewed-by: Arshad Hussain <arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Emoly Liu <emoly@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
